title: Christmas Carol Collection 2012
creator: Various
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox Christmas Carol Collection, 2012. LibriVox volunteers bring you this year's selection of 23 sacred and secular carols, hymns and Christmas songs, in English, French, German, Japanese and Latin. The collection comprises: 1. LATIN: Adeste Fideles Words and music by John Francis Wade (1711–1786), sung by Chessie Joy 2. GERMAN: Alle Jahre wieder Words: Wilhelm Hey (1789-1854); Music: Friedrich Philipp Silcher (1789-1860), sung by Julia Niedermaier 3. ENGLISH: Angels We Have Heard On High Traditional French, sung by Lyn Silva 4. FRENCH: Le Bon berger Author unknown, sung by Ezwa 5. ENGLISH: Carol of the Birds Words: William Lawrence Tomlins (1844-1930); Music: French anon, sung by Tony Oliva 6. ENGLISH:Child in the Manger Words: Ma­ry M. Mac­Don­ald (1789-1872), translated by Lachlan Macbean (1853-1931); Music: Trad. Scots ("Bun­es­san"), sung by Ryan DeRamos 7. ENGLISH: Come, Thou Long Expected Jesus words by Charles Wesley, 1745 music (Hyfrydol) by Rowland H. Prichard, 1830, sung by Laurie Anne Walden 8. GERMAN: Es ist ein Ros entsprungen 15th Century German carol arr. Michael Praetorius (c. 1571–1621), sung by Ruth Golding 9. ENGLISH: Gabriel's Message Words: Trad. Basque Trans. Sabine Baring Gould (1834−1924); Music: ’Gabriel‘s Message’ Traditional Basque Carol arr. (1922) Edgar Pettman (1866-1943), sung by Kristel Tretter 10. ENGLISH: God Rest You Merry, Gentlemen Traditional, arr. Lavinia Edna Walter; Lucy Etheldred Broadwood (d. 1929), sung by Tony Oliva 11. ENGLISH: He is Born Words: trans. Margaret Whitney Music: Old French, transcr. H. C. MacDougall (1858-1945), sung by Ruth Golding 12. ENGLISH: In The Bleak Midwinter Words: Christina Rossetti (1830-1894) Music: Gustav Holst (1874-1934), sung by Verity Kendall 13. FRENCH: Joyeux Noël Author unknown, sung by Ezwa 14. ENGLISH: The Kings Words: Henry Clough-Leighter (1874-1956); Music: Peter Cornelius (1824–1874), sung by Ruth Golding 15. FRENCH: Le Mage Author unknown, sung by Ezwa 16. JAPANESE: Mitsukai No Shunaru Ookimi (O Come, All Ye Faithful) 1922 Japanese hymnal, sung by Chessie Joy 17. FRENCH: Noël, Noël, jour de clémence Author unknown, sung by Ezwa 18. ENGLISH: O Come, O Come, Emmanuel Tr. John Mason Neale (1818-1866), sung by mlcui 19. ENGLISH: O Holy Night Words: John Sullivan Dwight (1813-1893); Music: Adolphe Charles Adam (1803-1856), sung by Chrissi 20. FRENCH: Patapan: ou Guillô, Pran Ton Tamborin par Bernard de La Monnoye (1641–1728), sung by Ruth Golding 21. GERMAN: Stille Nacht Music: Franz Xavier Gruber, Text: Joseph Mohr, sung by Kristel Tretter 22. FRENCH: Voici Noël Author unknown, sung by Ezwa 23. ENGLISH: Wexford Carol Traditional arr. Benjamin Bloomfield, sung by Robert G. Smith For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. Previous LibriVox carol collections may be found at: Christmas Carol Collection 2006 Christmas Short Works Collection 2008 (also includes spoken items) Christmas Carol Collection 2009 Christmas Carol Collection 2010 Christmas Carol Collection 2011 For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
